# Egress allowlist — one extended-regex per line, matched (case-insensitive) against
# the destination host. Anything not matched is DENIED (FilterDefaultDeny Yes).
# Keep this tight: it is the network half of the "no exfiltration" boundary. Package
# registries are included because a delivery legitimately runs `npm ci` / `pip install`;
# every entry widens the exfil surface — justify each.
#
# This is the BAKED DEFAULT. To permit an extra host (a private git host / registry)
# WITHOUT rebuilding the image, set GAFFER_EGRESS_ALLOW="host1,host2" or list hosts in
# $GAFFER_DATA/egress-allow.txt — sandbox-docker.sh renders those (regex-escaped +
# anchored, so they can't widen to match-all) on top of this file and mounts the result.

# --- the model endpoint (claude needs it) ---
(^|\.)anthropic\.com$

# --- JS / Node registries ---
(^|\.)npmjs\.org$
(^|\.)npmjs\.com$
(^|\.)nodejs\.org$
(^|\.)yarnpkg\.com$

# --- Python registries ---
(^|\.)pypi\.org$
(^|\.)pythonhosted\.org$

# --- source / package hosts commonly needed to fetch deps ---
(^|\.)github\.com$
(^|\.)githubusercontent\.com$
(^|\.)ghcr\.io$
